version: "^2.16.4" , ^ "Caret" tells that is can accept only minor and patch updates and ~ "till date" takes only patch updates, Agar major vale updates pe janaa hai to intensionally batana padega 

package-lock.json has got exact information of the version used in the project. If the project is run after two months, package-lock.json remembers which version was used in making.

If we have to share a project, node modules can not be shared to github, it is large in size, rather package.json and package-lock.json can be shared and after sharing in terminal, "npm install" it'll install the node modules package itself



